Description: Fragment of oval handle of a pottery transport amphora. Clay medium, brick red; thick dark grey core; white slip. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 102, 45? Similar ligatures are discussed by B.Schmaltz, Die Hellenistischen Amphorenstempel vom Kaunos (Asia Minor Studien 79) 350, KA813.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1321)
